This case has not been concluded. Unless a judgment of conviction is entered, the defendant is presumed innocent of all charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

1:47 pm - Prosecuting attorney Anthony A. Lambrecht in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Willie Hambright III appeared by video.  Attorney John Raymond Bilka appeared by video for Willie Hambright III. Defendant demands a preliminary hearing.  Preliminary hearing is set for 06-22-22 at 1:30 p.m. Br. 3
Preliminary hearing on June 22, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
Initial appearance on June 6, 2022 at 01:30 pm.

09:56 AM Defendant Willie Hambright III in court. Special appearance by Attorney Carl Knepel in court for the defendant. Attorney Jill L. Vendetti in court for State of Wisconsin. 
Public Defender has not appointed an attorney to represent the defendant. Defense was going to demand a preliminary hearing but requests that the initial be set over instead.
Initial appearance scheduled for June 6, 2022 at 01:30 pm.

BAIL HEARING - 
Defendant in custody and appearing by video from the Manitowoc County Jail.  The State informs the Court that the defendant will be charged with the crime of felony bail jumping.  The matter is continued for initial appearance on 05-02-22 at 1:30 p.m.  Bail is set at $1,000.00 recognizance bond with the conditions that he report to the Manitowoc County Sheriff's Department for fingerprints, photographs and identifying information within 48 hours or, if incarcerated, within 72 hours of release and defendant is not to operate a motor vehicle without a valid license.  Bail furnished and defendant is released from custody.
Minutes.
